infobox.description: The fourth most mutated consensus subnetwork (10.3% of all samples) includes KEAP1, NFE2L2, BPTF, CHD6, PTMA, RBM45, SLK, and WAC. This subnetwork is mutated in at least 10 samples of each cancer type with the exception of LAML (3 mutated samples). NFE2L2 is a transcription factor that modulates the response to oxidative stress and is normally sequestered in the cytoplasm by KEAP1 [38].
infobox.name: NFE2L2, KEAP1, and neighbors
